it.polimi.deib.p2pchat.discovery.services

Class ServiceList

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.deib.p2pchat.discovery.services.ServiceList

  • public class ServiceList
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that represents a list of WiFiP2pService. This list contains all the device found during discovery phase of the wifi direct protocol. This class use Singleton pattern.

    Created by Stefano Cappa on 04/02/15.

      • addServiceIfNotPresent

        public void addServiceIfNotPresent(WiFiP2pService service)
        Method to add a service inside the list in a secure way. The service is added only if isn't already inside the list.
        Parameters:
        service - WiFiP2pService to add.

      • getServiceByDevice

        public WiFiP2pService getServiceByDevice(WifiP2pDevice device)
        Method to get a service from the list, using only the device. This method use only the deviceAddress, not the device name, because sometimes Android doesn't get the name, but only the mac address.
        Parameters:
        device - WifiP2pDevice that you want to use to search the service.
        Returns:
        The WiFiP2pService associated to the device or null, if the device isn't in the list.

      • getElementByPosition

        public WiFiP2pService getElementByPosition(int position)
        Method to get a element using only the real position in the list (from 0 to n).
        Parameters:
        position - int that represents the position of the element.
        Returns:
        A WiFiP2pService element from the list at position. Attention, this method can throw a IndexOutOfBoundsException, if position < 0 || position >= size()
